00:14:41,013 --> 00:14:42,679
        Well, it wasn't         
        their home,             

236
00:14:42,780 --> 00:14:46,016
        But, yes,               
        I sold it, why?         

237
00:14:47,953 --> 00:14:50,587
Will the Nelson's               
still live in their house.      

238
00:14:50,688 --> 00:14:52,790
        Son, like I said,       
        it wasn't their house.  

239
00:14:52,891 --> 00:14:54,324
            It never was...     
            It was mine,        

240
00:14:54,425 --> 00:14:57,228
        And I don't know where  
        they're gonna live.     

241
00:14:57,329 --> 00:14:59,897
        People like the nelsons 
        and the Ingans--        

242
00:14:59,998 --> 00:15:01,032
        They'll survive somehow.

243
00:15:01,133 --> 00:15:02,599
                Hi kids.        

244
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:04,201
            Hi                  
    hi.                         

245
00:15:11,676 --> 00:15:13,344
                Hi, Margie.     

246
00:15:13,445 --> 00:15:16,547
        I'm afraid I have       
        some bad news for you.  

247
00:15:16,648 --> 00:15:18,816
                I'm sorry.      

248
00:15:22,286 --> 00:15:24,221
    Evicted?                    

249
00:15:53,985 --> 00:15:57,821
I would like to speak           
with a, uh, a Mr. ...           

250
00:15:59,157 --> 00:16:01,958
...Ribaldi, please.             

251
00:16:02,060 --> 00:16:04,094
                Come in.        

252
00:16:24,082 --> 00:16:28,652
Madame, the master              
will see you now.               

253
00:16:28,754 --> 00:16:34,591
You may enter and go as far     
as the carpet, and no further.  

254
00:16:34,692 --> 00:16:36,193
                The carpet...   
                Why?            

255
00:16:36,294 --> 00:16:38,862
To the carpet                   
and no further!                 

256
00:16:38,963 --> 00:16:41,432
If you cross the carpet         
or step onto it                 

257
00:16:41,533 --> 00:16:43,100
Or go any further,              

258
00:16:43,201 --> 00:16:47,438
Your interview will come        
to an abrupt end!               

259
00:16:47,539 --> 00:16:49,507
Do you understand?              

260
00:16:49,607 --> 00:16:51,375
                    Yes.        

261
00:17:04,456 --> 00:17:06,523
[ footsteps ]                   

262
00:17:09,227 --> 00:17:10,527
    Hello?                      

263
00:17:11,329 --> 00:17:15,866
            You may approach.   

264
00:17:16,802 --> 00:17:18,402
Your servant                    
said that I...                  

265
00:17:18,503 --> 00:17:20,337
             <i>Just three feet</i>    
             <i>towards the piano,</i> 

266
00:17:20,438 --> 00:17:22,606
         <i>Then stop in the light.</i>

267
00:17:22,707 --> 00:17:24,975
         <i>I want to look at you.</i> 

268
00:17:30,014 --> 00:17:31,648
May I come closer?              

269
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:34,184
    I like to see who           
    I'm talking to.             

270
00:17:34,285 --> 00:17:37,654
            No.                 
            State your business.

271
00:17:39,390 --> 00:17:42,325
You bought the old house        
on Patton street--              

272
00:17:42,427 --> 00:17:45,262
The one that belonged           
to James McBride.               

273
00:17:45,363 --> 00:17:49,233
It's our home and you--         
you evicted us today.           

274
00:17:49,334 --> 00:17:51,134
            What concern        
            is it of yours      

275
00:17:51,235 --> 00:17:54,171
            What I do           
            with my property?   

276
00:17:54,272 --> 00:17:57,407
If I lose my home,              
I could lose my job,            

277
00:17:57,508 --> 00:18:00,978
And without a job, my family    
would be in the street          

278
00:18:01,079 --> 00:18:02,679
We have nowhere to go.          

279
00:18:04,983 --> 00:18:07,618
            Tell me,            
            Mrs. Nelson,        

280
00:18:07,719 --> 00:18:11,288
            How valuable is     
            your home to you?   

281
00:18:11,389 --> 00:18:14,424
Well, I was paying Mr. McBride  
10 dollars a month,             

282
00:18:14,525 --> 00:18:16,961
And I am prepared               
to pay you 12.                  

283
00:18:17,062 --> 00:18:19,897
        [ chuckling ]           
        is your home            
        of no more value to you 

284
00:18:19,998 --> 00:18:22,466
        Than 10 or 12 dollars   
        a month?                

285
00:18:22,567 --> 00:18:23,967
Well, certainly it is!          

286
00:18:24,069 --> 00:18:26,970
What is this house              
worth to you?                   

287
00:18:27,071 --> 00:18:28,672
             <i>Very little.</i>       

288
00:18:28,773 --> 00:18:31,174
            You see, to me      
            this is a "house."  

289
00:18:31,275 --> 00:18:33,377
            Yours is a "home."  

290
00:18:33,478 --> 00:18:36,680
         <i>One is physical,</i>       
         <i>the other...Spiritual.</i> 

291
00:18:36,781 --> 00:18:38,949
            You, Mrs. Nelson,   
            of all people       

292
00:18:39,050 --> 00:18:42,352
    In this tiny little town    
    should know of such things. 

293
00:18:42,453 --> 00:18:43,854
    I should?                   

294
00:18:43,955 --> 00:18:45,555
                Yes.            

295
00:18:46,991 --> 00:18:49,126
Now, I ask you again--          

296
00:18:49,227 --> 00:18:52,663
            What value do you   
            place in your home? 

297
00:18:52,764 --> 00:18:53,997
I don't understand!             

298
00:18:54,098 --> 00:18:56,967
I don't have                    
anymore than--than that!        

299
00:18:58,269 --> 00:19:00,804
         <i>Think--</i>                
         <i>think for a moment--</i>   

300
00:19:00,906 --> 00:19:03,440
     <i>What is of greater value</i>   
     <i>to you than money?</i>         

301
00:19:03,541 --> 00:19:05,975
         <i>Than even your home?</i>   

302
00:19:07,078 --> 00:19:08,345
    My family.                  

303
00:19:08,446 --> 00:19:11,181
                 <i>Yes,</i>           
                 <i>your family.</i>   

304
00:19:11,282 --> 00:19:12,683
            More specifically,  
            your daughter--     

305
00:19:12,784 --> 00:19:14,851
            The one who sings.  

306
00:19:14,952 --> 00:19:16,720
Yes,                            
that's Bonnie.                  

307
00:19:16,821 --> 00:19:20,924
        If you want something   
        of great value from me, 

308
00:19:21,026 --> 00:19:22,459
            You must provide    
            something           

309
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:25,262
            That is of great    
            value yourself.     

310
00:19:25,363 --> 00:19:26,596
I am a poor woman.              

311
00:19:26,697 --> 00:19:28,532
I have nothing else             
to offer you.                   

312
00:19:28,633 --> 00:19:34,104
         <i>You may have your home</i> 
         <i>free on one condition--</i>

313
00:19:34,205 --> 00:19:35,839
        Bonnie will work here   

314
00:19:35,940 --> 00:19:38,041
            Each afternoon      
            as my servant.      

315
00:19:38,142 --> 00:19:39,910
             <i>As long as she</i>     
             <i>works for me,</i>      

316
00:19:40,011 --> 00:19:43,680
         <i>You will never want</i>    
         <i>for a place to live.</i>   

317
00:19:43,781 --> 00:19:46,283
    She's so young--            
    why not me?                 

318
00:19:46,384 --> 00:19:47,951
                Her tasks       
                will be simple. 

319
00:19:48,052 --> 00:19:50,453
                No harm         
                will befall her.

320
00:19:53,124 --> 00:19:55,392
        No.                     

321
00:19:55,493 --> 00:19:59,963
                No? No!         
                And why not?    

322
00:20:00,064 --> 00:20:04,301
Because you're--                
you're too cold...              

323
00:20:04,402 --> 00:20:07,304
And you're                      
too unfeeling!                  

324
00:20:07,405 --> 00:20:10,740
            Too cold?           

325
00:20:10,842 --> 00:20:13,310
                Too cold?       

326
00:20:13,411 --> 00:20:15,412
            What--you think me  
            without feeling     

327
00:20:15,513 --> 00:20:17,114
            Like a common beast?

328
00:20:17,215 --> 00:20:19,449
                Too cold?!      

329
00:20:19,550 --> 00:20:21,452
                 <i>Get out!</i>       

330
00:20:21,552 --> 00:20:23,053
                     <i>Get out!</i>   

331
00:20:23,154 --> 00:20:23,920
        I'm sorry...            

332
00:20:24,022 --> 00:20:26,289
                Leave! Be gone! 

333
00:20:26,390 --> 00:20:29,426
             <i>Never come back!</i>   

334
00:20:29,527 --> 00:20:31,328
    Get out!                    

335
00:20:32,764 --> 00:20:36,099
                     <i>Hans! Hans!</i>

336
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:39,603
        I think                 
        he wants you.           

337
00:20:39,704 --> 00:20:42,238
                 <i>Hans, come</i>     
                 <i>to me now!</i>     

338
00:20:42,340 --> 00:20:43,941
                 <i>You told me</i>    
                 <i>it would work!</i> 

339
00:20:44,042 --> 00:20:45,209
                 <i>You told me</i>    
                 <i>what to do!</i>    

340
00:20:45,310 --> 00:20:46,376
             <i>It didn't work!</i>    

341
00:20:46,477 --> 00:20:47,711
                 <i>How long</i>       
                 <i>must I wait?</i>   

342
00:20:47,812 --> 00:20:49,846
            How long must       
            I keep looking?     

343
00:20:49,947 --> 00:20:51,949
            Aaauuuuggghhhh!     

344
00:20:52,050 --> 00:20:54,851
Patience                        
is a virtue.                    

345
00:20:54,952 --> 00:20:57,887
                Patience        
                is a virtue?    

346
00:20:57,988 --> 00:21:04,594
    Get your sniveling,         
    pasty face out of here--now!

347
00:21:04,695 --> 00:21:08,165
            I don't know.       

348
00:21:08,266 --> 00:21:10,467
You told him no?                

349
00:21:10,568 --> 00:21:13,069
        Bonnie, you are not     
        working for that man.   

350
00:21:13,170 --> 00:21:14,171
    Why not?                    

351
00:21:14,272 --> 00:21:17,207
    Cuz there's something about 
    him that frightens me.      

352
00:21:17,308 --> 00:21:18,809
Like what?                      

353
00:21:18,910 --> 00:21:20,643
            It's like he's      
            hiding something--  

354
00:21:20,744 --> 00:21:22,579
            This dark secret.   

355
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:24,481
            He wouldn't even    
            let me see him.     

356
00:21:24,582 --> 00:21:26,149
        As we talked, he just   
        kept in the shadows,    

357
00:21:26,250 --> 00:21:27,684
            And then, when      
            he got angry,       

358
00:21:27,785 --> 00:21:30,487
            It was as if        
            he were this beast. 

359
00:21:30,588 --> 00:21:34,958
So...Either                     
we're homeless...               

360
00:21:35,059 --> 00:21:37,661
Or I go to work                 
for a person                    

361
00:21:37,762 --> 00:21:43,166
That's more like                
a beast than a man?             

362
00:21:43,267 --> 00:21:47,704
        Sweetheart,             
        this is not worth it.   

363
00:21:49,707 --> 00:21:50,774
    It's okay.                  

364
00:21:50,875 --> 00:21:52,042
    I don't mind.               

365
00:21:52,143 --> 00:21:54,511
Could it be worse               
than being homeless?            

366
00:21:54,612 --> 00:21:55,946
                Maybe.          

367
00:21:56,047 --> 00:21:58,348
Let me at least                 
try it for one day.             

368
00:21:58,449 --> 00:22:00,484
                He is different.

369
00:22:02,019 --> 00:22:07,491
But, being different            
doesn't make you bad...Does it? 

370
00:22:07,592 --> 00:22:11,962
        Most of the time, no.   
        But sometimes it does.  

371
00:22:13,631 --> 00:22:17,967
Well, there's only              
one way to find out.            

372
00:23:21,365 --> 00:23:25,535
                Bonnie, do you  
                see this door?  

373
00:23:25,636 --> 00:23:26,102
    Yes.                        

374
00:23:26,203 --> 00:23:27,571
            This door, here.    

375
00:23:27,672 --> 00:23:28,838
    I see it.                   

376
00:23:28,939 --> 00:23:34,778
        You must never,         
        never enter this room.  

377
00:23:34,879 --> 00:23:37,146
        Do you understand?      

378
00:23:39,083 --> 00:23:40,150
        I can't hear you.       

379
00:23:40,251 --> 00:23:40,984
I understand.                   

380
00:23:41,085 --> 00:23:43,253
            Good.               
            Follow me.          

381
00:23:47,225 --> 00:23:49,926
[ Hans: ]                       
Bonnie...                       

382
00:23:50,027 --> 00:23:54,464
             <i>What will happen</i>   
             <i>if I go in there?</i>  

383
00:23:56,401 --> 00:24:00,604
        Have you ever           
        heard the expression,   

384
00:24:00,705 --> 00:24:03,440
            "curiosity          
            killed the cat?"    

385
00:24:03,541 --> 00:24:05,642
    Yes.                        

386
00:24:05,743 --> 00:24:07,711
                Good.           

387
00:24:07,812 --> 00:24:09,412
                Now follow me.  

388
00:24:09,513 --> 00:24:13,182
So what will happen             
if I go into the room?          

389
00:24:19,991 --> 00:24:24,094
            The master resides  
            in that room.       

390
00:24:24,195 --> 00:24:26,596
            The master          
            desires his privacy 

391
00:24:26,697 --> 00:24:29,465
        More than anything      
        else in life.           

392
00:24:29,567 --> 00:24:32,869
        Should you invade       
        that privacy,           

393
00:24:32,970 --> 00:24:35,705
        You risk his anger.     

394
00:24:35,807 --> 00:24:40,210
                His anger can   
                be terrible.    

395
00:24:40,311 --> 00:24:43,647
                Do you          
                understand now? 

396
00:24:43,748 --> 00:24:46,616
So what will he do?             

397
00:24:51,422 --> 00:24:53,756
        If you promise me       

398
00:24:53,857 --> 00:24:58,595
        That you will never     
        go into that room,      

399
00:24:58,696 --> 00:25:02,899
        Then I'll see to it     
        that you receive        

400
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,368
        Whatever dessert        
        you want                

401
00:25:05,469 --> 00:25:07,037
Every night                     
you are here.                   

402
00:25:07,138 --> 00:25:09,205
          Banana split?         

403
00:25:09,306 --> 00:25:10,173
Certainly.                      

404
00:25:10,274 --> 00:25:11,908
        Deal.                   

405
00:25:12,009 --> 00:25:16,079
            Good.               
            Now, follow me.     

406
00:25:18,949 --> 00:25:21,384
[ Hans: ]                       
Bonnie!                         

407
00:25:25,522 --> 00:25:29,492
     <i>[ Dallin: ]</i>                
     <i>somebody bought my note,</i>   
     <i>demanding payment in full.</i> 

408
00:25:29,593 --> 00:25:32,796
                I gotta sell    
                my hogs to pay. 

409
00:25:32,897 --> 00:25:35,131
            You know I'd rather 
            see them pigs e't   

410
00:25:35,233 --> 00:25:36,300
            Than sold           
            like animals.       

411
00:25:36,401 --> 00:25:38,635
Them pigs is animals,           
ain't they?                     

412
00:25:38,736 --> 00:25:40,671
        It's that newcomer      
        banker sittin' up there 

413
00:25:40,772 --> 00:25:42,706
            On his high horse   
            buyin' and selling  

414
00:25:42,807 --> 00:25:44,741
        On other people's       
        misery and hard times.  

415
00:25:44,842 --> 00:25:47,243
Ain't no better                 
than your hogs, is he, pa?      

416
00:25:47,345 --> 00:25:49,579
            Boy, there's only   
            two differences     

417
00:25:49,680 --> 00:25:51,848
            Between my hogs     
            and a banker--      

418
00:25:51,949 --> 00:25:53,649
            A banker wears      
            expensive britches, 

419
00:25:53,751 --> 00:25:55,986
            And my hogs ain't   
            never stole nuthin'.

420
00:25:56,087 --> 00:25:57,820
        One of these days       
        somebody's gonna pull   

421
00:25:57,921 --> 00:25:59,923
        That rich newcomer      
        down off his high horse 

422
00:26:00,024 --> 00:26:01,758
            And teach him       
            a thing or two.     

423
00:26:01,859 --> 00:26:04,661
I hear                          
he's a monster.                 

424
00:26:04,762 --> 00:26:07,130
He's got teeth four inches      
sticking out of his mouth       

425
00:26:07,231 --> 00:26:08,998
To suck                         
the blood from.                 

426
00:26:09,099 --> 00:26:11,067
                Monster, huh?   

427
00:26:17,174 --> 00:26:19,275
      Where are you goin'?      

428
00:26:19,377 --> 00:26:21,344
                    Business.   

429
00:26:25,215 --> 00:26:27,317
                Hey, watch it!  

430
00:26:28,553 --> 00:26:29,686
            Hey!                

431
00:26:32,123 --> 00:26:33,222
    Look at this!               

432
00:26:33,323 --> 00:26:34,657
        Look at this            
        what I got today!       

433
00:26:34,758 --> 00:26:35,892
        Look at it!             

434
00:26:35,993 --> 00:26:38,828
    It's a notice on my butchers
    place of employment!        

435
00:26:38,929 --> 00:26:40,530
                Your note's     
                being called in.

436
00:26:40,631 --> 00:26:41,431
        Note?                   

437
00:26:41,532 --> 00:26:44,101
            Your place is       
            being taken away.   

438
00:26:44,202 --> 00:26:45,434
        You betcha!             

439
00:26:45,536 --> 00:26:47,737
    If they say I don't pay     
    by the end of next week!    

440
00:26:47,839 --> 00:26:49,205
             <i>[ Dallin: ]</i>        
             <i>see, and it ain't</i>  
             <i>just us two--</i>      

441
00:26:49,306 --> 00:26:51,408
         <i>There's lots of people</i> 
         <i>is bein' put out.</i>      

442
00:26:51,509 --> 00:26:53,309
    Times are hard now.         

443
00:26:53,410 --> 00:26:56,179
    Things are happening        
    all over the country.       

444
00:26:56,280 --> 00:26:59,149
            Ain't never happened
            t' me till now!     

445
00:26:59,250 --> 00:27:03,086
    And if it can happen to us, 
    ain't nobody safe           

446
00:27:03,187 --> 00:27:05,054
        From losin'             
        everything they got!    

447
00:27:05,155 --> 00:27:07,724
                 <i>Not even you!</i>  

448
00:27:10,227 --> 00:27:12,529
I suppose                       
you're right.                   

449
00:27:12,630 --> 00:27:14,998
        Who's doin' this        
        to us?                  

450
00:27:15,099 --> 00:27:17,867
That's hard to say...           

451
00:27:18,736 --> 00:27:21,037
            It ain't t' me.     

452
00:27:21,138 --> 00:27:23,440
    How's that?                 

453
00:27:23,541 --> 00:27:26,042
        All started when        
        that Ribaldi fella      

454
00:27:26,143 --> 00:27:29,045
             <i>Moved in up to the</i> 
             <i>old Silitoe place.</i> 

455
00:27:29,146 --> 00:27:32,716
                My money says,  
                it's him.       

456
00:27:32,817 --> 00:27:35,685
You can't be                    
sure it's him.                  

457
00:27:35,786 --> 00:27:39,556
Anybody could have              
bought those notes.             

458
00:27:39,657 --> 00:27:42,325
        Who's got money         
        to buy pig farm notes   

459
00:27:42,426 --> 00:27:44,895
        In castle gate?         

460
00:27:45,863 --> 00:27:47,430
    Dad?                        

461
00:27:51,836 --> 00:27:54,771
            Ain't you two       
            supposed to be home?

462
00:27:54,872 --> 00:27:59,008
Mom says to come                
and get you for supper.         

463
00:28:00,545 --> 00:28:01,611
            Go on home.         

464
00:28:01,712 --> 00:28:04,848
        Tell your mother        
        I'll be along soon.     

465
00:28:04,949 --> 00:28:07,050
                    Go on now.  

466
00:28:07,852 --> 00:28:10,687
C-c-come on home.               

467
00:28:10,788 --> 00:28:15,225
It ain't right you              
b-bein' alone like this.        

468
00:28:18,262 --> 00:28:20,964
            Go home, son...Now! 

469
00:28:23,968 --> 00:28:24,634
    B-b-but...                  

470
00:28:24,735 --> 00:28:26,202
            Didn't ya hear      
            what I said?        

471
00:28:26,303 --> 00:28:29,005
    Can't ya hear any better    
    than ya can talk?           

472
00:28:29,107 --> 00:28:30,940
                    Now get!    

473
00:28:31,675 --> 00:28:33,676
        Georgie! Porter!        

474
00:28:36,881 --> 00:28:38,481
        Hey, mister...          

475
00:28:38,582 --> 00:28:40,283
            That ain't right    
            what you did.       

476
00:28:40,384 --> 00:28:44,120
    I don't need you to tell me 
    what is and ain't right.    

477
00:28:44,222 --> 00:28:46,689
I noticed this new fella        
was up to no good.              

478
00:28:46,790 --> 00:28:48,925
    Why don't he go back        
    t' where he come from?      

479
00:28:49,026 --> 00:28:50,627
    Why's he                    
    gotta burden us?            

480
00:28:50,728 --> 00:28:52,062
        You talkin'             
        about fancy pants       

481
00:28:52,163 --> 00:28:53,396
        Up on the hill there?   

482
00:28:53,497 --> 00:28:55,231
I hear he's got                 
the little Nelson girl          

483
00:28:55,332 --> 00:28:57,133
Up there workin' for him.       

484
00:28:57,234 --> 00:28:59,269
            Ain't it enough     
            that our kids       

485
00:28:59,370 --> 00:29:00,937
            Have to eat         
            sugar and lard      

486
00:29:01,038 --> 00:29:02,638
            And wear rags       
            all the time?       

487
00:29:02,740 --> 00:29:06,309
        Why's he gotta have     
        'em cleaning for him?   

488
00:29:07,878 --> 00:29:11,147
        It ain't right...       
        That's all I'm sayin'.  

489
00:29:11,248 --> 00:29:13,482
            That fella's        
            danged strange.     

490
00:29:13,584 --> 00:29:16,052
            Never comes out     
            'cept at night.     

491
00:29:16,153 --> 00:29:19,622
             <i>My boy said he</i>     
             <i>saw him one night.</i> 

492
00:29:19,723 --> 00:29:21,891
    Saw him?                    

493
00:29:21,992 --> 00:29:23,493
         <i>Saw somethin'...</i>       

494
00:29:23,594 --> 00:29:26,229
    Looked like a man,          
        but...Different.        

495
00:29:26,330 --> 00:29:27,897
                Different?      

496
00:29:27,999 --> 00:29:30,767
        Only comes out not      
        in the sun...At night?  

497
00:29:30,868 --> 00:29:33,602
        Makes you think,        
            don't it?           

498
00:29:33,704 --> 00:29:35,772
        Listen,                 
        Bonnie's seen him.      

499
00:29:35,873 --> 00:29:39,576
    Mrs. Nelson doesn't         
    think there's a problem.    

500
00:29:39,677 --> 00:29:41,777
Maybe so,                       
but any man                     

501
00:29:41,879 --> 00:29:46,616
That would steal another man's  
land 'n' home is a monster!     

502
00:29:46,717 --> 00:29:49,152
I don't care                    
how he looks!                   

503
00:29:57,228 --> 00:30:02,565
[ Gabriella singing ]           
 %% un soffio mi rimane %%         

504
00:30:02,666 --> 00:30:08,405
 %% un giorno da passaro %%        

505
00:30:08,506 --> 00:30:16,613
 %% ancora do toto                
a te morendo %%                  

506
00:30:20,084 --> 00:30:24,921
 %% un' altra alb' presiosa %%     

507
00:30:25,022 --> 00:30:26,322
[ Ribaldi: ]                    
no! No! No!                     

508
00:30:26,423 --> 00:30:27,891
It's all the same!              

509
00:30:27,992 --> 00:30:30,126
You must take the music         
out of your throat              

510
00:30:30,227 --> 00:30:31,961
And put it                      
into your head!                 

511
00:30:32,063 --> 00:30:33,162
But what would you know?        

512
00:30:33,263 --> 00:30:35,365
You can't think                 
beyond your own face!           

513
00:30:35,466 --> 00:30:37,967
     <i>[ Gabriella: ]</i>             
     <i>it is you who cannot see</i>   
     <i>beyond your own face!</i>      

514
00:30:38,068 --> 00:30:39,302
     <i>Ever since</i>                 
     <i>you were wounded,</i>          

515
00:30:39,403 --> 00:30:40,770
     <i>You've let the</i>             
     <i>ugliness of your face</i>      

516
00:30:40,871 --> 00:30:42,138
     <i>Make your heart ugly!</i>      

517
00:30:42,239 --> 00:30:43,406
     <i>[ Gabriella: ]</i>             
     <i>how long must I wait?!</i>     

518
00:30:43,507 --> 00:30:44,641
     <i>Will you drive</i>             
     <i>this one away</i>              

519
00:30:44,742 --> 00:30:46,275
     <i>Like you've driven</i>         
     <i>all the others away?!</i>      

520
00:30:46,376 --> 00:30:47,443
[ Ribaldi: ]                    
enough, I said!                 

521
00:30:47,545 --> 00:30:49,012
     <i>[ Gabriella: ]</i>             
     <i>like you try</i>               
     <i>and drive me away?</i>         

522
00:30:49,113 --> 00:30:49,812
     <i>Ari,</i>                       
     <i>I love you!</i>                

523
00:30:49,913 --> 00:30:51,748
[ Ribaldi: ]                    
no, enough!                     

524
00:30:51,849 --> 00:30:54,817
I said enough!                  

525
00:30:54,918 --> 00:30:58,855
You came to sing,               
not lecture.                    

526
00:30:58,956 --> 00:31:04,027
[ piano ]                       

527
00:31:04,128 --> 00:31:09,432
[ Gabriella singing: ]          
 %% un soffio mi rimane %%         

528
00:31:09,533 --> 00:31:15,238
 %% un giorno da passaro %%        

529
00:31:15,339 --> 00:31:22,845
 %% ancora do toto                
a te morendo %%                  

530
00:31:26,350 --> 00:31:31,921
 %% un' altra alb' presiosa %%     

531
00:31:32,022 --> 00:31:37,293
 %% un' altra or' risveglia %%     

532
00:31:37,394 --> 00:31:44,467
 %% momento caru nei              
bracci tuio mi risposo. %%       

533
00:31:47,204 --> 00:31:49,272
            Ari, stop!          

534
00:31:49,373 --> 00:31:51,908
        Can't you see you've    
        frightened her?         

535
00:31:54,244 --> 00:31:57,580
    This is my...House.         

536
00:31:57,681 --> 00:32:00,083
         <i>[ Gabriella: ]</i>         
         <i>I don't care</i>           
         <i>whose house it is.</i>     

537
00:32:00,184 --> 00:32:02,885
    If you cannot speak to this 
    beautiful young woman,      

538
00:32:02,986 --> 00:32:04,521
    Then go away and pout.      

539
00:32:05,522 --> 00:32:08,124
            I said go!          

540
00:32:15,966 --> 00:32:18,301
Come with me Bonnie.            

541
00:32:18,402 --> 00:32:19,469
            You know my name.   

542
00:32:19,570 --> 00:32:21,971
[ Gabriella: ]                  
you're famous in this house.    

543
00:32:22,072 --> 00:32:23,740
You must not let                
the master frighten you.        

544
00:32:23,841 --> 00:32:25,941
He speaks                       
of you often.                   

545
00:32:26,810 --> 00:32:28,445
            Often?              

546
00:32:28,546 --> 00:32:32,482
Often.                          
You're a special girl.          

547
00:32:32,583 --> 00:32:34,283
But then all little             
girls are special.              

548
00:32:34,384 --> 00:32:36,686
Aren't they, Ari?               

549
00:32:39,556 --> 00:32:40,824
            Is that Ari?        

550
00:32:40,925 --> 00:32:42,692
    Yes.                        

551
00:32:42,793 --> 00:32:46,729
Ari and I have been             
friends for an eternity.        

552
00:32:46,830 --> 00:32:48,798
I suppose you could say         
that our road together          

553
00:32:48,899 --> 00:32:51,768
Has been long                   
and hard.                       

554
00:33:01,345 --> 00:33:05,115
Your lessons are refreshing,    
as well as frustrating.         

555
00:33:05,216 --> 00:33:09,486
            Then why do you     
            keep coming back?   

556
00:33:09,586 --> 00:33:12,155
        Why don't you stay      
        in your world of princes

557
00:33:12,256 --> 00:33:15,124
             <i>With dainty faces,</i> 
             <i>and white knights</i>  

558
00:33:15,225 --> 00:33:18,294
            Full of Grace       
            and pleasantries?   

559
00:33:22,265 --> 00:33:24,367
            Gabriella...        

560
00:33:41,751 --> 00:33:43,920
I will always come back,        

561
00:33:44,021 --> 00:33:47,256
Even though                     
we're worlds apart.             

562
00:33:55,666 --> 00:33:57,467
        Good-bye, Bonnie.       

563
00:33:57,568 --> 00:33:59,535
         <i>It was a pleasure</i>      
         <i>to meet you.</i>           

564
00:33:59,636 --> 00:34:02,371
             <i>Be brave.</i>          

565
00:34:21,791 --> 00:34:23,926
She's beautiful.                

566
00:34:25,428 --> 00:34:29,665
            You were told not   
            to enter this room. 

567
00:34:29,766 --> 00:34:32,602
I heard the music.              

568
00:34:32,703 --> 00:34:35,738
That woman--                    
who is she?                     

569
00:34:35,839 --> 00:34:38,874
        Her name is Gabriella.  

570
00:34:38,975 --> 00:34:42,044
        Gabriella is a Princess.

571
00:34:42,145 --> 00:34:43,813
A real Princess?                

572
00:34:43,914 --> 00:34:45,681
                 <i>I never lie.</i>   

573
00:34:45,782 --> 00:34:49,952
    A lie is a black hole that  
    grows deeper and deeper,    

574
00:34:50,053 --> 00:34:53,623
        Getting blacker         
        and blacker,            

575
00:34:53,723 --> 00:34:57,327
Swallowing everyone who         
happens to stumble into it.     

576
00:34:57,427 --> 00:34:59,061
Then when all                   
are consumed by it--            

577
00:34:59,162 --> 00:35:00,697
Friends, loved ones,            
family, all--                   

578
00:35:00,798 --> 00:35:03,399
            Do you know         
            what happens?       

579
00:35:03,500 --> 00:35:06,135
    What?                       

580
00:35:06,236 --> 00:35:10,039
            It turns into       
            a great black beast.

581
00:35:10,140 --> 00:35:16,746
        It turns on its creator 
        and devours him or her. 

582
00:35:18,582 --> 00:35:20,850
I never lie,                    
either.                         

583
00:35:22,352 --> 00:35:23,819
        That is good to know.   

584
00:35:23,921 --> 00:35:28,491
        Trust is the best way   
        to begin a relationship.

585
00:35:30,193 --> 00:35:33,096
        Now, tell me the truth--

586
00:35:33,197 --> 00:35:37,000
        Did you like what you   
        heard from Gabriella?   

587
00:35:37,101 --> 00:35:38,501
        It was beautiful.       

588
00:35:38,602 --> 00:35:40,203
Yes, it was.                    

589
00:35:40,304 --> 00:35:41,770
    In fact, you have           
    never heard anything        

590
00:35:41,871 --> 00:35:43,673
    Quite so beautiful          
    before, have you?           

591
00:35:43,774 --> 00:35:44,941
                No, never!      

592
00:35:45,042 --> 00:35:47,977
        And do you know why     
        Gabriella is the best?  

593
00:35:48,078 --> 00:35:50,579
She was born that way?          

594
00:35:51,782 --> 00:35:53,283
    Born that way?              

595
00:35:54,317 --> 00:35:55,851
    Born that way?              

596
00:35:55,953 --> 00:35:59,789
    No...And yes.               

597
00:35:59,890 --> 00:36:03,392
You see, many are born          
with what Gabriella has,        

598
00:36:03,493 --> 00:36:06,595
But few ever become             
what Gabriella is.              

599
00:36:06,696 --> 00:36:10,399
No, Gabriella is the best       
because I made her so.          

600
00:36:10,500 --> 00:36:14,336
She is the product              
of my genius.                   

601
00:36:14,437 --> 00:36:16,773
            You're not very     
            humble, are you?    

602
00:36:16,874 --> 00:36:17,873
Humble? Humble.                 

603
00:36:17,974 --> 00:36:21,678
No,                             
should I be?                    

604
00:36:21,778 --> 00:36:24,580
        Humility is a virtue,   
        Mr. Ribaldi.            

605
00:36:24,681 --> 00:36:27,083
            I should think      
            you should have     

606
00:36:27,184 --> 00:36:29,652
                A lot to be     
                humble about.   

607
00:36:31,755 --> 00:36:35,524
My, you are an honest           
little brute, aren't you?       

608
00:36:35,626 --> 00:36:38,193
So, what are you saying?        

609
00:36:38,295 --> 00:36:40,263
                Nothing.        

610
00:36:40,364 --> 00:36:43,399
That I am...Ugly?               

611
00:36:43,500 --> 00:36:48,070
            You're not...       
            "ugly", ugly.       

612
00:36:48,171 --> 00:36:50,806
Do not insult me.               

613
00:36:50,907 --> 00:36:52,742
What--you think                 
that I'm not ugly?              

614
00:36:52,843 --> 00:36:54,009
Where is honesty now?           

615
00:36:54,110 --> 00:36:58,547
            No...I mean yes...  
            I-I mean...         

616
00:36:58,648 --> 00:36:59,982
That I am ugly!                 

617
00:37:00,083 --> 00:37:01,184
You think that I am ugly!       

618
00:37:01,285 --> 00:37:04,153
Say it! Say it!                 

619
00:37:04,254 --> 00:37:05,455
                Yes, sir!       

620
00:37:05,555 --> 00:37:06,989
                You have        
                an ugly heart!  

621
00:37:07,090 --> 00:37:09,025
            That's worse than   
            having an ugly face!

622
00:37:09,126 --> 00:37:11,527
            You can't control   
            the way you look,   

623
00:37:11,628 --> 00:37:14,763
    But you can control         
    the way you treat others!   

624
00:37:14,864 --> 00:37:17,667
[ piano ]                       

625
00:37:19,436 --> 00:37:23,139
Yes, I am mean                  
and I am ugly.                  

626
00:37:23,240 --> 00:37:25,508
Now you may go.                 

627
00:37:31,047 --> 00:37:36,319
    Did you really teach her    
    to sing like that?          

628
00:37:36,420 --> 00:37:39,822
I did...Now go.                 

629
00:37:46,196 --> 00:37:47,129
                A beast?        

630
00:37:47,230 --> 00:37:49,198
[ Bonnie: ]                     
yes, just like you said.        

631
00:37:49,300 --> 00:37:51,367
And he acted                    
like one, too.                  

632
00:37:51,468 --> 00:37:53,669
    Then we're gonna have to    
    find another way to get by  

633
00:37:53,770 --> 00:37:55,938
        Because you're not gonna
        go back to that place.  

634
00:37:56,039 --> 00:37:58,707
But...There was something       
even more strange               

635
00:37:58,808 --> 00:38:00,343
Than the way                    
he looked.                      

636
00:38:00,444 --> 00:38:01,977
                Like what?      

637
00:38:02,078 --> 00:38:04,647
Well, he had a woman            
with him today,                 

638
00:38:04,748 --> 00:38:06,815
And she looked                  
just like a Princess            

639
00:38:06,917 --> 00:38:09,185
And sang like an Angel.         

640
00:38:09,286 --> 00:38:13,089
And he said that                
he taught her to sing.          

641
00:38:13,190 --> 00:38:15,524
And mom,                        
she loves him!                  

642
00:38:15,625 --> 00:38:19,762
How could he do                 
something so wonderful          

643
00:38:19,863 --> 00:38:22,865
If he's supposed                
to be so bad?                   

644
00:38:22,966 --> 00:38:25,201
And how could                   
someone so beautiful            

645
00:38:25,302 --> 00:38:27,169
Love someone so ugly?           

646
00:38:27,270 --> 00:38:28,271
            I don't know,       

647
00:38:28,372 --> 00:38:31,206
    But maybe there's something 
    more to Mr. Ribaldi         

648
00:38:31,308 --> 00:38:32,675
            Than meets the eye. 

649
00:38:32,776 --> 00:38:35,711
I wonder if...                  

650
00:38:35,812 --> 00:38:38,247
                What?           

651
00:38:38,348 --> 00:38:42,251
I wonder if he could            
teach me to sing like that?     

652
00:38:42,352 --> 00:38:45,455
            I'm afraid this     
            is not a fairy tale.

653
00:38:53,597 --> 00:38:54,563
        Wait for me!            

654
00:38:54,664 --> 00:38:55,631
Shhhhh!                         

655
00:38:55,732 --> 00:38:57,233
I told you                      
not to bring her!               

656
00:38:58,134 --> 00:39:00,236
            She said she'd tell 
            my pap if I didn't  

657
00:39:00,337 --> 00:39:02,037
                And he'd        
                woop me good!   

658
00:39:02,138 --> 00:39:03,772
        Look!                   

659
00:39:04,675 --> 00:39:07,042
Hey, look,                      
he's gone to bed.               

660
00:39:07,143 --> 00:39:09,278
Or going to work.               

661
00:39:09,380 --> 00:39:11,814
        You mean                
        sucking blood?          

662
00:39:11,915 --> 00:39:13,116
Yes.                            

663
00:39:13,217 --> 00:39:15,885
We don't know                   
if he's a blood sucker yet...   

664
00:39:15,986 --> 00:39:18,153
                 <i>...Do we?</i>      

665
00:39:18,254 --> 00:39:18,420
         Ooga ba goo-ga!        

666
00:39:20,791 --> 00:39:23,492
    [ screaming ]               

667
00:39:23,593 --> 00:39:27,496
Someone's gone 'n' chopped      
porter's head clean off!        

668
00:39:27,597 --> 00:39:29,865
          [ laughing ]          

669
00:39:29,966 --> 00:39:32,635
        Hey, what are you       
        guys doin' here?        

670
00:39:32,736 --> 00:39:35,304
    Come to peep on             
    the blood sucker.           

671
00:39:36,740 --> 00:39:40,009
[ Elaina:]                      
the blood sucker who got you    
captured up on the hill!        

672
00:39:40,110 --> 00:39:41,577
    They say                    
    he's a monster,             

673
00:39:41,678 --> 00:39:44,647
    And we've got               
    to get a look at him.       

674
00:39:44,748 --> 00:39:45,847
[ Bonnie: ]                     
Mr. Ribaldi?                    

675
00:39:45,948 --> 00:39:47,316
                    Yup.        

676
00:39:47,417 --> 00:39:49,519
            There isn't         
            any blood sucker,   

677
00:39:49,620 --> 00:39:52,688
            And there certainly 
            isn't any monster.  

678
00:39:52,789 --> 00:39:55,190
        Mr. Ribaldi is just...  

679
00:39:55,292 --> 00:39:56,926
    ...A monster?               

680
00:39:57,027 --> 00:39:58,427
                    No.         

681
00:39:58,528 --> 00:40:00,863
            He's just different,
            that's all.         

682
00:40:00,964 --> 00:40:04,433
C-can ya p-prove it?            

683
00:40:04,534 --> 00:40:06,969
                Porter, you too?

684
00:40:07,070 --> 00:40:09,372
                You don't       
                believe me?     

685
00:40:09,473 --> 00:40:14,109
Everyb-body                     
in t-town says it.              

686
00:40:15,879 --> 00:40:17,813
            Look,               
            come back tomorrow  

687
00:40:17,914 --> 00:40:19,615
            And I'll take you   
            to meet him.        

688
00:40:19,716 --> 00:40:20,950
            It's too late now.  

689
00:40:21,051 --> 00:40:22,584
        Tomorrow he'll          
        be a man again.         

690
00:40:22,685 --> 00:40:23,719
        We want to see          
        him tonight             

691
00:40:23,820 --> 00:40:26,789
        Before he--he...        
        You know whats.         

692
00:40:26,890 --> 00:40:29,125
                No,             
                I don't know.   

693
00:40:29,226 --> 00:40:30,926
                Have you        
                ever heard      

694
00:40:31,027 --> 00:40:33,396
                That "curiosity 
                kills the cat?" 

695
00:40:33,497 --> 00:40:36,632
         I ain't a cat.         
            Let's go.           

696
00:40:36,733 --> 00:40:38,734
        Ain't you comin'?       

697
00:40:38,835 --> 00:40:41,337
                Nope.           
                I don't peeper! 

698
00:40:56,286 --> 00:40:57,653
        See anything?           

699
00:40:57,754 --> 00:40:59,254
    Nothin'.                    

700
00:41:05,295 --> 00:41:08,531
        [ door creaking ]       

701
00:41:11,935 --> 00:41:14,770
T-t-ommy...                     
Ni-ni-Nick...                   

702
00:41:18,341 --> 00:41:19,842
        Hey, guys,              

703
00:41:19,943 --> 00:41:22,144
             <i>There's somebody</i>   
             <i>in here.</i>           

704
00:41:22,245 --> 00:41:23,312
             Elaina!            

705
00:41:23,413 --> 00:41:25,515
She's going                     
into the house!                 

