00:58:12,253 --> 00:58:14,020
[ piano ]                       

943
00:58:14,121 --> 00:58:17,591
I'll try to be                  
better with Hans.               

944
00:58:17,692 --> 00:58:20,794
[ porter's dad: ]               
why do we gotta have            
beans every single night?       

945
00:58:20,895 --> 00:58:22,028
I'm sick and tired of this!     

946
00:58:22,129 --> 00:58:23,763
We could have a little meat     
sometimes, couldn't we?         

947
00:58:23,865 --> 00:58:25,766
What--what are you doing        
with all the money?             

948
00:58:25,867 --> 00:58:27,901
I know it isn't much!           

949
00:58:28,002 --> 00:58:31,838
<i>You're taking it and using it</i>   
<i>on them kids all the time!</i>      

950
00:58:31,939 --> 00:58:34,741
What are you using              
it for anyway?                  

951
00:58:36,411 --> 00:58:38,611
Of course,                      
she needs a new pair of shoes?  

952
00:58:38,712 --> 00:58:40,013
We could all                    
use a new pair...               

953
00:58:40,114 --> 00:58:41,014
        Is dad mad again?       

954
00:58:41,116 --> 00:58:42,782
            Yeah.               

955
00:58:44,853 --> 00:58:46,753
        Whatcha doin'?          

956
00:58:46,854 --> 00:58:49,823
    I'm g-going out.            

957
00:58:49,924 --> 00:58:51,925
            Out where?          

958
00:58:52,026 --> 00:58:57,331
                I d-dunno.      
                Just out.       

959
00:58:57,432 --> 00:59:01,535
            Don't t-tell mom    
            and d-dad.          

960
00:59:01,636 --> 00:59:04,271
[ yelling continues ]           

961
00:59:12,246 --> 00:59:15,515
[ Dallin: ]                     
bills, bills, bills!            

962
00:59:18,185 --> 00:59:21,588
 I figure if I sell all my hogs,
     we can keep the place.     

963
00:59:21,690 --> 00:59:23,757
      My goodness, Emelda,      

964
00:59:23,858 --> 00:59:25,492
        Who'd a knowd           
        a man would be forced   

965
00:59:25,593 --> 00:59:28,495
        To sell his family      
        just to keep his home.  

966
00:59:28,596 --> 00:59:29,697
We'll get through.              

967
00:59:29,798 --> 00:59:31,398
We've still got                 
the farm.                       

968
00:59:31,499 --> 00:59:33,567
We can start again.             

969
00:59:37,405 --> 00:59:39,472
     Telegram from Denver...    

970
00:59:43,778 --> 00:59:45,145
             <i>Who do you know</i>    
             <i>in Denver?</i>         

971
00:59:45,246 --> 00:59:47,347
    I don't know.               

972
00:59:47,448 --> 00:59:49,550
        Well, here.             

973
00:59:49,651 --> 00:59:52,586
    It's from the Winchester    
    clinic in Denver.           

974
00:59:52,687 --> 00:59:54,988
             <i>Winchester clinic?</i> 

975
00:59:55,089 --> 01:00:00,927
    It says my condition        
    can be reversed.            

976
01:00:01,029 --> 01:00:04,464
    I'm to go to Denver         
    as soon as possible.        

977
01:00:04,565 --> 01:00:06,199
              Here,             
        let me see that.        

978
01:00:06,300 --> 01:00:09,570
      We never seen nobody      
  in Denver about no condition. 

979
01:00:09,671 --> 01:00:14,073
 Besides, we ain't got the money
     for that sort of thing.    

980
01:00:21,282 --> 01:00:23,483
[ giggling ]                    

981
01:00:28,356 --> 01:00:30,123
         <i>[ Dallin: ]</i>            
         <i>well, Emelda Avery--</i>   

982
01:00:30,224 --> 01:00:33,927
     <i>You's a</i>                    
     <i>ten "thousandaire"...Ha!</i>   

983
01:00:57,385 --> 01:00:58,751
Who are you?                    

984
01:00:58,853 --> 01:01:02,055
        Perhaps, I should be    
        asking you that.        

985
01:01:02,156 --> 01:01:05,359
    I'm p-porter.               

986
01:01:05,460 --> 01:01:10,129
    I'm a friend                
    of b-Bonnie's.              

987
01:01:10,230 --> 01:01:15,168
        Yes, Bonnie speaks      
        highly of you.          

988
01:01:15,269 --> 01:01:17,371
    Really?                     

989
01:01:17,472 --> 01:01:19,406
        She tells me            
        you've got a problem.   

990
01:01:19,507 --> 01:01:21,641
                Sit down.       

991
01:01:37,891 --> 01:01:41,161
There is nothing more mean      
     and ugly in this world     

992
01:01:41,262 --> 01:01:46,833
 Than to have a beautiful gift, 
        a loving spirit,        

993
01:01:46,934 --> 01:01:49,802
         <i>And a desire to give</i>   
         <i>and share these things</i> 

994
01:01:49,904 --> 01:01:53,640
         <i>When there is nobody</i>   
         <i>to share them with.</i>    

995
01:01:56,244 --> 01:02:00,247
      You know what I mean,     
    don't you, porter?          

996
01:02:00,348 --> 01:02:03,984
             <i>Is it your father?</i> 

997
01:02:04,085 --> 01:02:05,685
        [ crying: ]             
        I hate it.              

998
01:02:05,786 --> 01:02:08,355
        I hate my d-d-dad.      

999
01:02:11,292 --> 01:02:13,860
                 <i>Do you know</i>    
                 <i>what I think?</i>  

1000
01:02:13,961 --> 01:02:15,996
        W-w-what?               

1001
01:02:16,097 --> 01:02:18,865
             <i>I think that you</i>   
             <i>love your father</i>   

1002
01:02:18,966 --> 01:02:21,968
          And you hate          
        the way you feel.       

1003
01:02:22,069 --> 01:02:25,872
         Change the way         
            you feel.           

1004
01:02:25,973 --> 01:02:27,741
        He doesn't              
        deserve love!           

1005
01:02:27,842 --> 01:02:29,675
    He's mean and selfish!      

1006
01:02:29,777 --> 01:02:31,645
    He doesn't care about us!   

1007
01:02:31,746 --> 01:02:34,013
        He only cares           
        about himself.          

1008
01:02:34,114 --> 01:02:35,382
        I hate him!             

1009
01:02:35,483 --> 01:02:36,917
        He should love us!      

1010
01:02:37,018 --> 01:02:39,953
        He should take us       
        hiking and fishing      

1011
01:02:40,054 --> 01:02:42,455
        And teach us            
        how to play ball...     

1012
01:02:49,196 --> 01:02:54,501
  Sometimes it takes hard times 
  to make us gentle and strong. 

1013
01:02:54,602 --> 01:02:56,703
How can it do both?             

1014
01:02:56,804 --> 01:03:00,374
It just makes my dad mean.      

1015
01:03:00,475 --> 01:03:02,909
    Meanness isn't strength.    

1016
01:03:03,010 --> 01:03:06,246
        Your father             
     is not a strong man...     

1017
01:03:06,347 --> 01:03:09,449
         Not yet anyway.        

1018
01:03:09,550 --> 01:03:12,419
            But who knows what  
            tomorrow brings.    

1019
01:03:12,520 --> 01:03:15,054
        You mustn't             
         give up on him.        

1020
01:03:15,156 --> 01:03:17,057
        He needs the love       
    of his family now,          

1021
01:03:17,158 --> 01:03:18,725
        Just as you need        
            his love.           

1022
01:03:18,826 --> 01:03:22,862
        And someday you will    
        both get what you need. 

1023
01:03:24,799 --> 01:03:27,367
             <i>Do you</i>             
             <i>see this mirror?</i>   

1024
01:03:28,970 --> 01:03:30,570
        Yeah.                   

1025
01:03:30,671 --> 01:03:33,773
         <i>It's a magic mirror.</i>   

1026
01:03:34,642 --> 01:03:36,843
        Like in snow white?     

1027
01:03:36,944 --> 01:03:39,946
    Now that you mention it,    
    I think it was snow white   

1028
01:03:40,047 --> 01:03:43,850
         <i>Who gave this mirror</i>   
         <i>to me as a gift.</i>       

1029
01:03:43,951 --> 01:03:46,820
             <i>If you look deeply</i> 
             <i>into the mirror</i>    

1030
01:03:46,921 --> 01:03:50,390
     <i>And tell yourself what</i>     
     <i>you've learned tonight,</i>    

1031
01:03:50,491 --> 01:03:55,495
  The mirror will show you how  
 you've been made a better man. 

1032
01:03:55,596 --> 01:03:57,930
I don't understand.             

1033
01:03:58,032 --> 01:04:00,534
            You d-d-d-don't?    

1034
01:04:07,041 --> 01:04:09,542
        Wow!                    

1035
01:04:11,512 --> 01:04:14,047
So, you have Cyrano who has     
a nose about a foot long        

1036
01:04:14,148 --> 01:04:16,483
Afraid to tell Roxanne          
he loves her.                   

1037
01:04:16,584 --> 01:04:17,583
She's too beautiful,            

1038
01:04:17,684 --> 01:04:19,552
And he's afraid                 
that she'll laugh at him.       

1039
01:04:19,653 --> 01:04:20,854
Can you imagine it?             

1040
01:04:20,955 --> 01:04:22,522
A guy who just                  
the night before                

1041
01:04:22,623 --> 01:04:26,759
Successfully dueled 100         
assailants scared of a woman!   

1042
01:04:26,861 --> 01:04:28,628
So what does                    
he do about it?                 

1043
01:04:28,729 --> 01:04:31,698
He hires the handsomest man     
he can, named Christian,        

1044
01:04:31,799 --> 01:04:33,966
To "woo" the beautiful Roxanne  

1045
01:04:34,067 --> 01:04:36,770
By saying the things            
that Cyrano writes for him.     

1046
01:04:36,871 --> 01:04:38,471
Well,                           
it just so happens              

1047
01:04:38,572 --> 01:04:40,774
That Roxanne falls in love      
with Christian,                 

1048
01:04:40,875 --> 01:04:42,909
But not because he's handsome,  

1049
01:04:43,010 --> 01:04:45,412
But because he expresses        
a beautiful soul                

1050
01:04:45,513 --> 01:04:47,914
By the things                   
he says and writes.             

1051
01:04:48,015 --> 01:04:50,583
Problem is that Christian       
also loves Roxanne,             

1052
01:04:50,684 --> 01:04:53,120
But can't tell her              
because he has a hard time      

1053
01:04:53,221 --> 01:04:55,255
Expressing his feelings...      

1054
01:04:55,356 --> 01:04:57,390
    So who get's the girl?      

1055
01:04:57,491 --> 01:05:00,026
            You have to read    
            the play.           

1056
01:05:00,127 --> 01:05:04,097
                This is         
                very strange.   

1057
01:05:04,198 --> 01:05:08,635
    %% memimamo memimamo         
    memimamo memimamo mou. %%    

1058
01:05:08,736 --> 01:05:13,806
[ Bonnie and Hans: ]            
 %% memimano memimamo             
memimamo memimamo mou. %%        

1059
01:05:13,907 --> 01:05:15,608
             Hans...            

1060
01:05:15,709 --> 01:05:17,210
    How many times              
    have I told you             

1061
01:05:17,311 --> 01:05:20,580
    That it hurts my ears       
    to hear you sing?           

1062
01:05:21,815 --> 01:05:25,385
        Perhaps I could give    
        you a lesson or two.    

1063
01:05:25,486 --> 01:05:27,453
    Really!                     

1064
01:05:27,555 --> 01:05:29,289
Did you hear that?              

1065
01:05:29,389 --> 01:05:32,392
The master is going             
to give me a lesson!            

1066
01:05:32,493 --> 01:05:35,295
Do you think I'll               
ever be any good?               

1067
01:05:35,396 --> 01:05:37,030
                No.             

1068
01:05:37,131 --> 01:05:39,332
            Play.               

1069
01:05:43,537 --> 01:05:47,774
Now, Georgie, I have            
something for you.              

1070
01:05:54,214 --> 01:05:57,484
         %% dolce amor %%         

1071
01:05:57,585 --> 01:06:01,054
    %% figlietta divan %%         

1072
01:06:01,155 --> 01:06:04,357
    %% sei un fiore in gemma %%   

1073
01:06:04,458 --> 01:06:09,495
      %% sbocciando vicin. %%     

1074
01:06:09,596 --> 01:06:12,799
        %% aprile sei tu %%       

1075
01:06:12,900 --> 01:06:16,970
      %% ma sogni di giun. %%     

1076
01:06:17,071 --> 01:06:19,706
 %% eogni giorno passando, %%      

1077
01:06:19,807 --> 01:06:23,309
    %% t'inbel lezza di piu. %%   

1078
01:06:24,846 --> 01:06:27,914
 %% dear April child, %%           

1079
01:06:28,015 --> 01:06:31,384
 %% are you dreaming of June? %%   

1080
01:06:31,485 --> 01:06:34,287
 %% like a tender young flower %%  

1081
01:06:34,388 --> 01:06:38,925
 %% awaiting Summer's bloom. %%    

1082
01:06:39,026 --> 01:06:45,698
 %% sweet April child,            
in the springtime of youth, %%   

1083
01:06:45,799 --> 01:06:48,368
 %% what a glorious season, %%     

1084
01:06:48,469 --> 01:06:52,305
 %% it is yours,                  
let it shine through %%          

1085
01:06:52,406 --> 01:06:58,277
 <i> %% ti sveglia Cara figlia %% </i>     

1086
01:06:58,378 --> 01:07:03,449
  <i> %% of what begins to to wake. %% </i>

1087
01:07:03,550 --> 01:07:09,623
   <i> %% in fondo sieigia Bella. %% </i>  

1088
01:07:09,723 --> 01:07:18,231
  <i> %% let it grow inside of you. %% </i>

1089
01:07:21,002 --> 01:07:25,172
    There's something strange   
    goin' on around here.       

1090
01:07:25,273 --> 01:07:28,308
    I used to think papanickolas
    was superstitious,          

1091
01:07:28,409 --> 01:07:31,811
        But there is something  
        strange goin' on.       

1092
01:07:45,326 --> 01:07:50,096
 <i> %% ti sveglia Cara figlia %% </i>     

1093
01:07:50,197 --> 01:07:55,134
  <i> %% of what begins to to wake. %% </i>

1094
01:07:55,235 --> 01:08:00,073
 <i> %% in fondo seigia Bella %% </i>      

1095
01:08:00,174 --> 01:08:07,313
 %% let it grow inside of you %%   

1096
01:08:07,414 --> 01:08:10,149
 %% sweet April child, %%          

1097
01:08:10,250 --> 01:08:13,453
 %% it's the spring               
of your youth. %%                

1098
01:08:13,554 --> 01:08:16,222
 %% cherish these Precious days, %% 

1099
01:08:16,323 --> 01:08:20,727
 %% Summer comes all too soon %%   

1100
01:08:20,828 --> 01:08:27,333
 %% dear April child,             
still dreaming of June. %%       

1101
01:08:29,403 --> 01:08:32,305
    Yeah, there's some strange, 
    strange things happening,   

1102
01:08:32,406 --> 01:08:34,173
            That's for sure.    

1103
01:08:34,274 --> 01:08:36,342
            Makes me wonder     
            what's wrong?       

1104
01:08:36,443 --> 01:08:38,945
Makes me wonder                 
what's right.                   

1105
01:08:40,014 --> 01:08:42,481
            Mom, I'm home.      

1106
01:08:49,423 --> 01:08:52,892
Bonnie, I'm afraid that they    
have some some bad news.        

1107
01:09:01,068 --> 01:09:02,201
            I'm sorry, honey.   

1108
01:09:02,302 --> 01:09:04,003
            I know              
            how much singing    

1109
01:09:04,104 --> 01:09:05,738
            In the contest      
            meant to you.       

1110
01:09:05,839 --> 01:09:08,174
Listen, Mr. McBride             
left me a message.              

1111
01:09:08,275 --> 01:09:10,943
He said that if you stop        
working for Mr. Ribaldi,        

1112
01:09:11,044 --> 01:09:13,879
They'd allow you to sing        
in the contest.                 

1113
01:09:13,980 --> 01:09:16,750
[ Ribaldi, shouting: ]          
I don't know why                
I allowed myself                

1114
01:09:16,851 --> 01:09:18,584
To be talked into listening     
to your croaking!               

1115
01:09:18,685 --> 01:09:20,019
A frog has better cords!        

1116
01:09:20,120 --> 01:09:22,555
I've heard yaks in the          
high Andes belch in Harmony     

1117
01:09:22,656 --> 01:09:24,123
Compared to your bellowings!    

1118
01:09:24,225 --> 01:09:26,292
    I take umbrage              
    at the insinuation.         

1119
01:09:26,393 --> 01:09:28,461
Insinuation?                    
Who's insinuation?              

1120
01:09:28,562 --> 01:09:30,096
I might have charges            
brought against you             

1121
01:09:30,197 --> 01:09:31,464
For polluting the air!          

1122
01:09:31,565 --> 01:09:33,566
    He thinks                   
    I'm getting better.         

1123
01:09:36,337 --> 01:09:38,037
        Bonnie!                 

1124
01:09:38,138 --> 01:09:42,675
A Ray of sunshine               
on this...Irksome day.          

1125
01:09:44,345 --> 01:09:46,879
Now,                            
come soothe my soul.            

1126
01:09:52,019 --> 01:09:56,422
I think you are finally ready,  
so I want you to have this.     

1127
01:10:02,529 --> 01:10:04,097
It's a song.                    

1128
01:10:04,198 --> 01:10:07,934
I wrote it a long time ago      
when times were better.         

1129
01:10:08,035 --> 01:10:09,335
                Better?         

1130
01:10:09,437 --> 01:10:12,472
Happier...                      
At least for myself.            

1131
01:10:21,549 --> 01:10:23,883
You've been awakened.           

1132
01:10:23,984 --> 01:10:24,918
                What?           

1133
01:10:25,019 --> 01:10:29,322
Awakened...                     
To the truth.                   

1134
01:10:29,423 --> 01:10:31,557
You see, you bear               
the blush of a young girl       

1135
01:10:31,658 --> 01:10:35,394
Who has come                    
face-to-face with reality.      

1136
01:10:35,495 --> 01:10:38,230
Reality and all it's ugliness.  

1137
01:10:38,331 --> 01:10:42,001
[ piano ]                       

1138
01:10:42,102 --> 01:10:43,970
        They won't let me       
        go to the competition   

1139
01:10:44,071 --> 01:10:46,338
             <i>Unless I stop</i>      
             <i>working for you.</i>   

1140
01:10:46,440 --> 01:10:49,908
     <i>Mom says they think</i>        
     <i>you're taking their homes.</i> 

1141
01:10:51,245 --> 01:10:53,646
        You're not, are you?    

1142
01:10:53,748 --> 01:10:55,848
Does it matter?                 

1143
01:10:58,752 --> 01:11:00,586
            It does to me.      

1144
01:11:02,889 --> 01:11:05,625
No, I haven't taken anything    
from these people.              

1145
01:11:05,725 --> 01:11:07,460
            I didn't think      
            you could.          

1146
01:11:07,561 --> 01:11:10,095
            Why don't you       
            tell them.          

1147
01:11:10,196 --> 01:11:15,268
Because people hear and see only
what they want to hear and see. 

1148
01:11:15,369 --> 01:11:17,337
What I say can't                
get past their eyes,            

1149
01:11:17,438 --> 01:11:20,840
Let alone                       
into their ears.                

1150
01:11:20,941 --> 01:11:23,709
Now go.                         
I understand.                   

1151
01:11:35,956 --> 01:11:38,724
            Where were we?      

1152
01:11:39,660 --> 01:11:42,361
    What?                       

1153
01:11:42,462 --> 01:11:44,097
            My lesson.          

1154
01:11:44,198 --> 01:11:46,165
    Lesson?                     

1155
01:11:49,370 --> 01:11:54,106
You're the most beautiful person
      that I've ever known.     

1156
01:11:54,207 --> 01:11:55,908
You don't mean that.            

1157
01:11:57,845 --> 01:12:01,581
You don't think I'd let         
those people tell me what to do!

1158
01:12:01,682 --> 01:12:04,083
I won't leave you!              

1159
01:12:09,623 --> 01:12:11,190
            No.                 

1160
01:12:11,892 --> 01:12:15,461
            You must go now...  
            Quickly.            

1161
01:12:15,562 --> 01:12:17,697
    Why?                        

1162
01:12:17,797 --> 01:12:20,166
    Because neither you         
    or I want to waste          

1163
01:12:20,267 --> 01:12:23,703
All that we've accomplished     
     this last little while.    

1164
01:12:23,804 --> 01:12:25,705
            When you go         
            to that competition,

1165
01:12:25,805 --> 01:12:27,907
            You and I will      
            have triumphed.     

1166
01:12:28,008 --> 01:12:30,910
            If you don't,       
            we will have failed.

1167
01:12:31,011 --> 01:12:33,546
         <i>You will go</i>            
         <i>to that competition,</i>   

1168
01:12:33,647 --> 01:12:35,748
        And you will win!       

1169
01:12:35,849 --> 01:12:40,119
 You will be everything that you
 ever dreamed of being and more!

1170
01:12:41,455 --> 01:12:43,055
        Not for yourself,       

1171
01:12:43,156 --> 01:12:45,258
         <i>But for what you</i>       
         <i>give to others.</i>        

1172
01:12:45,359 --> 01:12:46,258
    But I...                    

1173
01:12:46,359 --> 01:12:48,494
                     <i>No buts!</i>   

1174
01:12:48,595 --> 01:12:52,131
            Our time together   
            is fulfilled.       

1175
01:12:52,232 --> 01:12:55,301
            Now you must go     
            and never come back 

1176
01:12:55,402 --> 01:12:58,737
    Or all that we have         
    accomplished will be wasted!

1177
01:12:58,839 --> 01:13:02,441
            Now go.             
            Go now and sing!    

1178
01:13:03,810 --> 01:13:05,745
                Sing!           

1179
01:13:12,352 --> 01:13:14,586
        I'll be with you.       

1180
01:13:31,838 --> 01:13:34,640
Is she...Gone?                  

1181
01:13:40,614 --> 01:13:44,116
She chose not to stay?          

1182
01:13:46,419 --> 01:13:49,055
        She chose to stay.      

1183
01:13:49,156 --> 01:13:51,991
She chose to stay?              

1184
01:13:52,092 --> 01:13:53,793
            I practically had   
            to chase her away!  

1185
01:13:53,893 --> 01:13:55,361
She chose to stay?              

1186
01:13:55,462 --> 01:13:57,263
                Ha, ha, ha...   

1187
01:13:57,364 --> 01:13:58,864
            She chose me!       

1188
01:14:00,100 --> 01:14:01,834
She chose to stay?              

1189
01:14:06,006 --> 01:14:07,640
[ piano ]                       

1190
01:14:07,741 --> 01:14:10,175
 %% heir, heir meistro... %%        

1191
01:14:13,414 --> 01:14:16,749
    Do you wish to wound        
    this moment of happiness?   

1192
01:14:44,311 --> 01:14:48,514
...You listen                   
to what he has to say.          

1193
01:14:50,450 --> 01:14:51,283
            I love you,         
            sweetheart.         

1194
01:14:51,384 --> 01:14:53,352
                 <i>I love you.</i>    

1195
01:14:55,422 --> 01:14:57,123
Hans,                           
take care of her.               

1196
01:14:57,224 --> 01:14:59,291
I wish I could go,              
but I've gotta work.            

1197
01:14:59,392 --> 01:15:01,294
        She will be just fine.  

1198
01:15:01,395 --> 01:15:04,196
    Okay...                     

1199
01:15:06,232 --> 01:15:08,000
                Bye, Bonnie!    

1200
01:15:08,101 --> 01:15:10,803
            Bye, Bonnie!        
            I hope you win!     

1201
01:15:10,904 --> 01:15:12,972
            Good luck, Bonnie.  

1202
01:15:24,117 --> 01:15:26,652
            Hello, Georgie.     

1203
01:15:26,753 --> 01:15:28,020
    Hello.                      

1204
01:15:28,121 --> 01:15:30,789
What can I do for you?          

1205
01:15:36,897 --> 01:15:43,035
Can you teach me to sing...     
Like you taught Bonnie?         

1206
01:15:43,136 --> 01:15:46,905
            Do your parents     
            know where you are? 

1207
01:15:51,378 --> 01:15:54,780
        Someday I may teach you 
        how to sing, Georgie.   

1208
01:15:54,881 --> 01:15:57,717
            But, today          
            is not that day.    

1209
01:15:57,818 --> 01:16:01,120
        Now come, I'll take you 
        part of the way home.   

1210
01:16:15,368 --> 01:16:17,169
    Aren't you coming?          

1211
01:16:17,271 --> 01:16:19,038
[ Ribaldi: ]                    
is there no other way?          

1212
01:16:19,139 --> 01:16:22,208
    This is a short cut.        

1213
01:16:23,443 --> 01:16:27,312
Perhaps the long way            
would be preferable this time.  

1214
01:16:29,049 --> 01:16:31,216
        Come on, we play here   
        all the time.           

1215
01:16:31,318 --> 01:16:32,485
    Georgie, wait!              

1216
01:16:32,586 --> 01:16:35,187
    This place                  
    looks dangerous!            

1217
01:16:35,288 --> 01:16:36,088
Georgie!                        

1218
01:16:36,189 --> 01:16:37,557
[ Georgie screams ]             

1219
01:16:37,658 --> 01:16:39,525
            Georgie!            

1220
01:16:54,607 --> 01:16:57,810
                Gee, it's like  
                a church...     

1221
01:16:57,911 --> 01:17:00,179
                Only bigger.    

1222
01:17:00,280 --> 01:17:03,248
    In many ways                
    it is a church.             

1223
01:17:03,350 --> 01:17:05,451
    For that reason,            

1224
01:17:05,552 --> 01:17:10,823
It will not frighten you--      
it will inspire you.            

1225
01:17:10,924 --> 01:17:12,625
                    Thanks.     

1226
01:17:13,994 --> 01:17:16,996
Two more lost                   
their homes--today!             

1227
01:17:17,097 --> 01:17:19,565
That Don Duncan                 
and Kevin welsh.                

1228
01:17:19,666 --> 01:17:21,300
            Well, you know      
            those fellas...     

1229
01:17:21,401 --> 01:17:25,171
I know they wasn't much         
in the way of being men,        

1230
01:17:25,272 --> 01:17:27,973
But nobody should lose          
their houses like that!         

1231
01:17:28,074 --> 01:17:29,609
                    Hi, son.    

1232
01:17:31,177 --> 01:17:33,512
Georgie hasn't come home        
from school yet.                

1233
01:17:33,614 --> 01:17:34,713
            Well, where is she? 

1234
01:17:34,814 --> 01:17:35,581
I don't know.                   

1235
01:17:35,682 --> 01:17:36,615
We've been looking              
all over.                       

1236
01:17:36,716 --> 01:17:38,550
Mom's out lookin'               
right now.                      

1237
01:17:38,651 --> 01:17:40,219
                    Come on.    

1238
01:17:42,156 --> 01:17:45,925
Uh, Gordon, your girl,          
Georgie, she's a missing?       

1239
01:17:46,026 --> 01:17:47,493
                Yeah.           

1240
01:17:47,594 --> 01:17:48,460
    That's no good.             

1241
01:17:48,562 --> 01:17:49,929
    Hey,                        
    we gotta help him!          

1242
01:17:50,030 --> 01:17:51,163
    Come on, let's go!          

1243
01:17:51,264 --> 01:17:52,731
     %% the birds in June, %%     

1244
01:17:52,833 --> 01:17:54,933
    %% they sing their cheery    
        fa la la la la. %%       

1245
01:17:55,034 --> 01:17:57,236
     %% the birds they swoon     
     and laugh so dearly, %%     

1246
01:17:57,337 --> 01:17:58,704
    %% fa la la la la. %%         

1247
01:17:58,805 --> 01:18:02,507
      %% all who sing along      
join in springtime song, %%      

1248
01:18:02,609 --> 01:18:08,314
  %% fa la la la la la la la. %%  

1249
01:18:08,415 --> 01:18:10,282
[ applause ]                    

1250
01:18:10,383 --> 01:18:12,117
    She's good.                 

1251
01:18:12,219 --> 01:18:15,087
            So are you.         

1252
01:18:15,188 --> 01:18:16,088
Put the map down.               

1253
01:18:16,190 --> 01:18:17,022
Let's look at the map.          

1254
01:18:17,123 --> 01:18:18,858
        Where are we            
        on this map?            

1255
01:18:20,027 --> 01:18:21,360
Where are we not?               

1256
01:18:21,461 --> 01:18:23,195
     [ indistinct chatter ]     

1257
01:18:32,539 --> 01:18:37,075
     %% in the mountain still    
     while my love sleeps, %%    

1258
01:18:37,176 --> 01:18:41,513
 %% I climb to yonder hill. %%     

1259
01:18:47,654 --> 01:18:49,121
[ woman screams ]               

1260
01:18:53,292 --> 01:18:54,693
     [ indistinct chatter ]     

1261
01:18:54,794 --> 01:18:57,496
[ bell on door rings ]          

1262
01:18:57,597 --> 01:18:58,797
[ woman screams ]               

1263
01:18:58,899 --> 01:19:00,166
    Georgie!                    

1264
01:19:00,267 --> 01:19:02,301
    Georgie, honey!             

1265
01:19:03,236 --> 01:19:05,137
            She fell!           

1266
01:19:05,238 --> 01:19:07,740
It's true...                    
He is a monster.                

1267
01:19:11,712 --> 01:19:14,680
What was she                    
doing with you?                 

1268
01:19:14,781 --> 01:19:17,849
        Is she going            
        to be all right?        

1269
01:19:17,951 --> 01:19:20,553
    Georgie!                    

1270
01:19:20,654 --> 01:19:23,589
The monster...                  
He must a done something to her.

1271
01:19:29,195 --> 01:19:30,262
            Get him!            

1272
01:19:30,363 --> 01:19:33,465
    [ yelling and screaming ]   

1273
01:19:35,635 --> 01:19:38,003
[ applause ]                    

1274
01:19:38,104 --> 01:19:41,039
Thank you, Kathleen Hamilton    
of castle gate.                 

1275
01:19:41,140 --> 01:19:46,178
Next, Bonnie Nelson singing an  
original composition by Ribaldi.

1276
01:19:54,888 --> 01:20:00,559
 %% music boxes have within %%     

1277
01:20:00,661 --> 01:20:06,965
     <i> %% melodies they</i>            
     <i>carry with them. %% </i>         

1278
01:20:07,067 --> 01:20:14,406
     <i> %% once they're opened,</i>     
     <i>music fills the air. %% </i>     

1279
01:20:18,845 --> 01:20:30,389
 %% every person you have known   
has a song of their own. %%      

1280
01:20:30,490 --> 01:20:39,565
     <i> %% once they open up</i>        
     <i>you'll hear what's there. %% </i>

1281
01:20:39,666 --> 01:20:42,434
    %% it's not easy, %%          

1282
01:20:42,535 --> 01:20:46,972
        %% you must listen       
        with your heart %%       

1283
01:20:47,073 --> 01:20:51,243
    %% for what lies hidden. %%   

1284
01:20:51,344 --> 01:21:00,785
     <i> %% there was a melody</i>       
     <i>locked deep inside of me, %% </i>

1285
01:21:00,886 --> 01:21:05,357
     <i> %% but now it's free. %% </i>     

1286
01:21:05,458 --> 01:21:09,861
     <i> %% it found a place</i>         
     <i>embraced by Harmony, %% </i>     

1287
01:21:09,962 --> 01:21:13,398
     <i> %% sweet Harmony. %% </i>         

1288
01:21:13,499 --> 01:21:23,242
 %% love more than anything       
teaches our hearts to sing. %%   

1289
01:21:23,343 --> 01:21:29,581
    %% only love                 
    could break the shell, %%    

1290
01:21:29,682 --> 01:21:43,929
    %% now I know very well      
    the love within myself. %%   

1291
01:21:44,030 --> 01:21:45,397
        [ gunshot ]             

1292
01:21:50,002 --> 01:21:52,605
            Stop it!            

1293
01:21:52,706 --> 01:21:55,874
         You don't know         
    what you're doing.          

1294
01:21:55,976 --> 01:21:59,411
          So just leave         
         this man alone!        

1295
01:22:01,514 --> 01:22:03,082
    Somebody help me.           

1296
01:22:03,183 --> 01:22:04,749
    Somebody please help me!    

1297
01:22:04,850 --> 01:22:07,619
        I say we go up to that  
        castle in the Sky       

1298
01:22:07,721 --> 01:22:09,788
    And see what the monster's  
    done to us all!             

1299
01:22:09,889 --> 01:22:11,724
          [ cheering ]          

1300
01:22:11,825 --> 01:22:14,993
    [ screaming ]               
    will nobody help me?!       

1301
01:22:15,094 --> 01:22:16,061
                Get his feet!   

1302
01:22:16,162 --> 01:22:17,696
            Take his feet!      

1303
01:22:17,797 --> 01:22:26,972
      %% there was a melody      
locked deep inside of me, %%     

1304
01:22:27,073 --> 01:22:31,243
     %% but now it's free. %%     

1305
01:22:31,344 --> 01:22:35,648
    %% it found a place          
      embraced by Harmony,      

1306
01:22:35,749 --> 01:22:39,385
    %% sweet Harmony. %%          

1307
01:22:39,486 --> 01:22:49,694
 %% love more than anything       
teaches our hearts to sing. %%   

1308
01:22:49,795 --> 01:22:55,234
     <i> %% only love</i>                
     <i>could break the shell, %% </i>   

1309
01:22:55,335 --> 01:23:12,685
    %% now, I know very well     
    the love within myself. %%   

1310
01:23:14,320 --> 01:23:17,489
          [ applause ]          

1311
01:23:27,400 --> 01:23:30,602
     [ indistinct shouting ]    

1312
01:23:40,313 --> 01:23:44,850
[ glass breaking,               
crashing ]                      

1313
01:24:08,241 --> 01:24:12,811
[ applause ]                    

1314
01:24:25,558 --> 01:24:26,558
            I got it!           

1315
01:24:26,659 --> 01:24:28,893
         I got the book!        

1316
01:24:28,994 --> 01:24:30,963
    [ glass breaking ]          

1317
01:24:38,571 --> 01:24:41,306
          [ shouting ]          

1318
01:24:41,407 --> 01:24:42,874
            I got the proof!    

1319
01:24:42,975 --> 01:24:44,743
            I got the book      
            to show 'em         

1320
01:24:44,844 --> 01:24:48,514
        What the monster has    
        been doin' to us all!   

1321
01:24:48,615 --> 01:24:49,514
            Read it!            

1322
01:24:49,615 --> 01:24:51,917
[ Dallin: ]                     
yeah, here we go!               

1323
01:24:52,819 --> 01:24:54,519
        Rufus Ellington!        

1324
01:24:54,620 --> 01:24:56,388
              Yeah!             

1325
01:24:56,489 --> 01:24:59,992
        Andre Ellington!        

1326
01:25:00,093 --> 01:25:00,992
             Andre?             

1327
01:25:01,093 --> 01:25:06,131
          Near sighted,         
    $ 450.00...He sees.         

1328
01:25:06,232 --> 01:25:09,401
[ woman: ]                      
let's hear about the land!      

1329
01:25:11,137 --> 01:25:15,173
        Julie Johnson,          
        broken femur--          

1330
01:25:17,109 --> 01:25:20,345
        $700.00...              

1331
01:25:22,515 --> 01:25:24,783
             Walks.             

1332
01:25:25,317 --> 01:25:26,785
                 <i>Julie?</i>         

1333
01:25:26,886 --> 01:25:30,488
        He did that             
        for my Julie?           

1334
01:25:39,532 --> 01:25:42,634
        [ quietly ]             
        Steve sorter...         

1335
01:25:54,247 --> 01:25:57,582
          Steve sorter,         
      son of Mitch Sorter,      

1336
01:25:57,683 --> 01:26:02,888
        Club foot,              
      $ 1,300.00--he walks.     

1337
01:26:07,460 --> 01:26:10,428
                 <i>Emelda Avery.</i>  

1338
01:26:10,529 --> 01:26:14,032
          Emelda Avery,         
     tumor at base of spine,    

1339
01:26:14,133 --> 01:26:20,005
     Crippled, $ 10,000.00--    
         will walk soon.        

1340
01:26:35,188 --> 01:26:36,822
    I don't get it.             

1341
01:26:36,923 --> 01:26:40,893
    Who's been takin'           
    our homes?!                 

1342
01:26:40,994 --> 01:26:43,061
            Me!                 

1343
01:26:46,065 --> 01:26:48,600
        It was me.              

1344
01:26:48,702 --> 01:26:53,571
        I'm the one             
      that took your land.      

1345
01:26:53,672 --> 01:26:57,542
     So if you want to hurt     
     somebody, then hurt me.    

1346
01:26:58,744 --> 01:27:01,846
        But please leave        
         this man alone.        

1347
01:27:06,953 --> 01:27:08,954
            Let's go.           

1348
01:27:09,054 --> 01:27:11,923
        There's been enough harm
        done tonight already.   

1349
01:27:12,025 --> 01:27:14,626
                Son...          

1350
01:27:29,142 --> 01:27:32,644
                [ crying ]      

1351
01:27:32,745 --> 01:27:36,381
        Come on, we'd better get
        this man to a hospital. 

1352
01:27:43,856 --> 01:27:45,190
Good man.                       

1353
01:27:45,291 --> 01:27:47,659
Will you come                   
back tomorrow?                  

1354
01:27:47,760 --> 01:27:49,394
    Hey, I was told two bucks   
    for a day's work.           

1355
01:27:49,495 --> 01:27:51,830
            Yeah, yeah, yeah,   
            I know that.        

1356
01:27:57,003 --> 01:27:58,336
        What happened?          

1357
01:27:58,437 --> 01:28:02,474
They t-t-took him.              

1358
01:28:02,575 --> 01:28:04,676
        Where is he?            

1359
01:28:06,212 --> 01:28:07,546
        What happened?          

1360
01:28:07,647 --> 01:28:09,314
            He pulled Georgie   
            from the culvert.   

1361
01:28:09,415 --> 01:28:12,184
                He saved her.   

1362
01:28:12,285 --> 01:28:14,919
        Where is he?            

1363
01:28:15,021 --> 01:28:17,555
                He died         
                this morning.   

1364
01:28:23,996 --> 01:28:28,166
 %% ah, ah, ah, ah, ah... %%       

1365
01:29:18,450 --> 01:29:22,620
        Well, I suppose it's    
        off to the east for me. 

1366
01:29:22,721 --> 01:29:24,523
What will you do?               

1367
01:29:24,624 --> 01:29:27,826
            I'm...Going home.   

1368
01:29:27,927 --> 01:29:29,061
    Where's that?               

1369
01:29:29,162 --> 01:29:31,696
            Oh,                 
            a far off land.     

1370
01:29:31,797 --> 01:29:35,166
        So distant you'd        
        never know it existed.  

1371
01:29:35,268 --> 01:29:39,037
        I've been re-employed   
        by an old patron.       

1372
01:29:39,138 --> 01:29:40,505
Well then,                      
you're happy.                   

1373
01:29:40,607 --> 01:29:42,807
        Definitely.             

1374
01:29:42,908 --> 01:29:45,676
        Well,                   
        good-bye.               

1375
01:29:45,778 --> 01:29:48,513
        It has been wonderful.  

1376
01:29:53,719 --> 01:29:56,388
            I wish I could      
            say as much.        

1377
01:29:58,123 --> 01:29:59,891
We need                         
to get on home.                 

1378
01:29:59,992 --> 01:30:02,327
    Timmy...Timmy...            
    Timmy.                      

1379
01:30:12,538 --> 01:30:14,639
            C'mere.             

1380
01:30:16,876 --> 01:30:20,946
    S-s-ure c-c-cleaned         
    things up in a hurry.       

1381
01:30:21,047 --> 01:30:21,779
[ music playing ]               

1382
01:30:21,880 --> 01:30:23,081
                Listen!         

1383
01:30:23,182 --> 01:30:23,949
                    What is it? 

1384
01:30:24,050 --> 01:30:25,117
            That's my song!     

1385
01:30:25,218 --> 01:30:27,619
            Mr. Ribaldi         
            gave it to me.      

1386
01:30:37,262 --> 01:30:39,030
May I help you?                 

1387
01:30:39,131 --> 01:30:43,735
        No, I thought you       
        were somebody else.     

1388
01:30:43,836 --> 01:30:47,672
    I'm sorry, my daughter      
    has had a bad experience.   

1389
01:30:47,773 --> 01:30:50,141
        I'm sorry.              
          What was it?          

1390
01:30:50,242 --> 01:30:51,643
        May I help?             

1391
01:30:51,744 --> 01:30:54,679
[ Bonnie: ]                     
no, it wasn't bad.              

1392
01:30:54,780 --> 01:30:57,449
            In fact,            
            it was wonderful.   

1393
01:30:57,549 --> 01:30:59,384
    I'm sorry                   
    to bother you.              

1394
01:30:59,485 --> 01:31:01,652
        No problem.             

1395
01:31:01,754 --> 01:31:04,122
[ Bonnie's mom: ]               
we need to go.                  

1396
01:31:19,372 --> 01:31:20,839
    Who are you?                

1397
01:31:20,940 --> 01:31:22,407
    Why are you here?           

1398
01:31:22,508 --> 01:31:23,575
Bonnie...                       

1399
01:31:23,676 --> 01:31:25,543
                    No,         
                    it's okay.  

1400
01:31:25,644 --> 01:31:29,081
    I used to live here         
        a long time ago.        

1401
01:31:29,182 --> 01:31:30,815
I was just passing through      

1402
01:31:30,916 --> 01:31:32,217
        And thought             
     I'd take one last look     

1403
01:31:32,318 --> 01:31:34,218
          Before I left         
            for home.           

1404
01:31:34,320 --> 01:31:35,720
            Where's home?       

1405
01:31:35,821 --> 01:31:37,489
                    Far away.   

1406
01:31:37,589 --> 01:31:40,525
    So far away I'd never       
    thought it existed?         

1407
01:31:40,626 --> 01:31:44,362
            Some might put it   
            that way, yes.      

1408
01:31:44,464 --> 01:31:47,098
